OTHER VALUABLE FEATURES ON THE TIP SITE INCLUDE:

Search TIP with the Verity search engine at the top right-hand
corner of each page.
--------------------------------------------------
Buyers Guide
http://www.tipmagazine.com/ptbg/search.jsp
--------------------------------------------------
Find a job
http://www.aip.org/careersvc/
--------------------------------------------------
Event calendar
http://www.tipmagazine.com/cal/eventhome.jsp
--------------------------------------------------
Indexes
Every issue of TIP is available online, from inception in July 1995
to the current time. There are five indexes:
Chronological, which lists the contents of each issue by date
http://www.tipmagazine.com/tip/pastiss.html
News stories, which lists news stories by title, author, issue, and
page numbers, from the latest to the earliest.
http://www.tipmagazine.com/tip/news.html
Feature articles, which lists news stories by title, author, issue,
and page numbers, from the latest to the earliest.
http://www.tipmagazine.com/tip/features.html
Departments, which lists every department that ever ran in TIP, with
all the stories that ran in each department, including title,
author, issue, and page numbers, from the latest to the earliest.
http://www.tipmagazine.com/tip/departments.html
New products, which includes every new product in TIP, showing
company name, product description, issue, and page number. These are
listed alphabetically by company name, but may be reordered by a
click to alphabetical by product name or chronological by
publication date.
http://www.tipmagazine.com/tip/newproducts1.html
--------------------------------------------------
Print copies of past issues may be ordered.
http://www.tipmagazine.com/tip/reprints.html

*********************************

THE INDUSTRIAL PHYSICIST (TIP) is a colorful, award-winning
bimonthly magazine published by The American Institute of Physics,
with a print circulation of 60,000. Articles are targeted at
physicists working in industry, but our readers also include
engineers, computer programmers, and a wide range of scientific
professionals and their managers. The magazine helps busy people
stay  abreast of cutting edge technology by providing easily
digested, interesting  stories about scientific developments that
are going to make a difference in the commercial world.
